name: R Markdown y cierre del año!
description:
Se viene el último evento del año! Y tenemos el taller de R Markdown para cerrar con broche de oro!!!

R Markdown permite escribir informes reproducibles y dinámicos con R.  Podés usarlo para incluir código R y resultados en presentaciones, documentos pdf, html, Word y mas. Este taller está pensado desde un nivel básico-intermedio, así que no te preocupes si recién empiezas a codear en R.  Para aprovecharlo traé tu laptop con R y RStudio instalados (para más info de cómo hacer esto:https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B0X9hdtcUykTdy1ZaVM3S3hxQ0k.

Si creés que te vendría bien una intro a R o un repaso antes de venir, hacé click aquí para ir al repositorio donde encontrarás todos los materiales de nuestros encuentros anteriores.

Después del taller tendremos un espacio reservado para hacer sociales, así nos conocemos entre todxs y podemos compartir ideas para el próximo año. Este se realizará en el restaurant del Museo Evita, el consumo aprox. es de 150 pesos y además habrá torta especial de R-Ladies para todxs!

Se vienen más detalles en unos días, por lo pronto revisá tu agenda y reservá tu lugar en el taller! Si confirmás asistencia pero luego no podés asistir, te pedimos por favor que dejes tu lugar disponible para otra persona ya que el espacio es limitado. Y si no podés asistir, el día de la reunión anunciaremos el acceso al streaming del evento. 


Cualquier consulta no dudes en escribirnos por meetup, slack o fb.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

****El evento se realizará en el auditorio del Museo Evita, para llegar se toma la entrada del restaurant, el auditorio está subiendo al escalera que está a la derecha en el patio del restaurant****


*** Para asegurarte que tu notebook está lista para trabajar en el taller, si es posible, por favor, actualizá tu versión de R y RStudio. También para instalar los paquetes necesarios para el taller, desde RStudio seguí estos pasos:


1) File -> New file -> R Markdown...


2) Se abrirá un cuadro de diálogo, hacé clic en "Ok"


3) Se abrirá un script de R "Untitled 1", apretá Ctrl+Shift+K


4) Pedirá grabar el archivo, ponéle un nombre y hacé clic en "Ok"


5) Si necesitás instalar paquetes, RStudio te avisará y lo hará. Si todo va bien, al final se abrirá una ventana mostrando un documento que comienza con la palabra "Untitled". Cerrá todo, ya estás lista para el taller.


Si surge algún problema durante este proceso, avisános por meetup, Slack o llegá un ratito antes al taller así tratamos de solucionarlo entre todas****

Saludos!

name: Inaugural meeting
description:
Paris’ first R Programming Community for Ladies! This is a non-profit coding club for all R proficiency levels, whether you're a new or aspiring R user, or an experienced female R programmer interested in mentoring, networking, and maybe picking up some new skills. We are a community designed to encourage, support and ultimately drive the development of our own R skills through a range of events, including meetups where members tackle hands-on tutorials and exercises to learn specific functionalities, informal gatherings, talks about latest trends, and debates; we will also share information about relevant external events. Our goal is to promote access to STEM careers and tools for women (trans and cis) and gender-variant people. Additionally, we support the Free Software Movement and the global R Community!


Links to the slides will be posted in the comments.

To better understand members’ skill levels and topics of potential interests, we’ve created a short survey. Please fill it out, even if you cannot attend the meeting, so we can pick speakers and topics that are most interesting to you.

________________________

La première communauté française de programmeuses R ! R-Ladies Paris est un meetup à but non lucratif pour les programmeuses R de tous niveaux, que vous soyez débutantes ou agueRries, intéressées par du tutorat, du réseau ou simplement pour venir acquérir de nouvelles compétences en R... La communauté R-Ladies Paris est née du souhait d’encourager, soutenir et faire connaître R à travers une large gamme de rencontres comme des ateliers où les participantes peuvent pratiquer sur des fonctionnalités R, des réunions informelles, des présentations sur les dernières tendances et des débats... Nous relaierons également les événements jugés pertinents pour la communauté. Notre objectif est de promouvoir l’accès aux carrières scientifiques, techniques et mathématiques aux femmes (cis et trans) et variants de genre. Par ailleurs, nous sommes ferventes supportrices du mouvement Open Source et de la communauté R.

Les liens vers la presentation dans les commentaires après le meetup.

Afin d’en savoir plus sur vos compétences et vos sujets d’intérêts, nous avons créé ce questionnaire. Sentez-vous libre de la remplir même si vous ne pensez pas pouvoir participer au prochain meetup afin d’élaborer des contenus en adéquation avec vos envies :)
how_to_find_us: Come to the main entrance, we will open the door for you until the start of the meetup. Rendez-vous à l'entrée principale : nous vous y attendrons jusqu'au début du meetup

name: Introduction to interactive visualizations with Shiny (Tutorial)
description:
Shiny is a powerful tool that allows you to deploy your R scripts to the web in the form of interactive apps. At this meeting we’ll go over how to make a Shiny app from scratch. This is meant as a beginner tutorial, however if you already have experience with Shiny you are still welcome to attend as some additional topics will be covered. You can also help out others in the practical bits and chime in with recommendations, we'd appreciate an interactive session. In addition to Shiny we’ll be using map data to plot data from the past  US presidential elections.

Before coming to the meet-up please: 1) install RStudio, 2) be sure the libraries “shiny”, “tidyverse”, “maps”, and “mapproj” are installed, 3) download the GitHub repository to have the data and any other files necessary for the tutorial, and 4) don't forget to bring your laptop!

For general discussions and to connect with other RLadies, join our Facebook group.

______________________________________________

Shiny est une puissante application web qui facilite le déploiement de développements R sous forme interactive et dynamique. Lors de ce meetup nous construirons une application Shiny de A à Z. Ce tutoriel est destiné aux grandes débutantes mais si vous avez déjà pratiqué Shiny, soyez les bienvenues : d’autres sujets seront abordés. Vous pouvez également venir en aide aux autres participantes avec des astuces pratiques et prodiguer conseils et recommandations : nous n’avons rien contre l’interactivité dans ce format de rencontre. En plus de Shiny, nous utiliserons des données spatiales issues des élections présidentielles américaines du passé.

Avant qu’on se retrouve : 1) installer RStudio 2) vérifier que les bibliothèques suivantes sont installées, “shiny”, “tidyverse”, “maps”, et “mapproj”, 3) les données nécessaires au tutoriel sont disponibles au téléchargement sur ce repo GitHub, assurez-vous de télécharger le tout avant le jour, 4) et n’oubliez pas d’emmener votre ordinateur !

Nous vous rappelons par ailleurs que vous pouvez nous rejoindre sur le groupe Facebook afin d’y rencontrer d’autres RLadies, y parler de R...ou pas :-)
how_to_find_us: We will be on the 2nd floor, look for the signs. If the door is closed, a portier should be there to let you in. Otherwise we will post a number you can call. Nous serons cette fois au 2nd : suivez les flèches !

name: Manipulation de données avec dplyr (tutoriel)
description:
Ce meetup en français est dédié à la manipulation de données avec le package dplyr du tidyverse. Nous verrons comment importer des données, les fusionner, les nettoyer, en faire des statistiques descriptives... Nous expérimenterons la stratégie dite du "split-apply-combine" et l'opérateur %>% n'aura plus de secrets pour vous. N'oubliez pas vos ordinateurs ! 

Les données sont à downloader grâce à ces 2 lignes de code : https://github.com/rladies-paris/RLadies_dplyr_2016-12-12/blob/master/data.R dans le repo de la présentation de ce soir qui sera mis à jour à la fin de la présentation (https://github.com/rladies-paris/RLadies_dplyr_2016-12-12)

In this French-speaking meetup, we'll have a gentle introduction to data cleaning and data wrangling with the dplyr package of the tidyverse. We'll import some data, join them, clean them...We'll experiment together the "split-apply-combine" strategy and the %>% operator will no longer have any secrets from you. Don't forget your laptops !


Data : https://github.com/rladies-paris/RLadies_dplyr_2016-12-12/blob/master/data.R

Repo : https://github.com/rladies-paris/RLadies_dplyr_2016-12-12

name: Creating reproducible reports and journal articles using RMarkdown
description:
When writing a report based on data, one usually has to rely on copying and pasting figures and results between a statistical programming environment of choice (of course, we prefer R) and a document editor. This is no longer necessary, thanks to integrated documents that can process data, generate figures, and produce text.
After discussing the basics and reasoning of RMarkdown, we will go through a working example of writing a paper or report, including formatting it in the infamous APA style. We'll then talk about best practices, advantages, and disadvantages of writing integrated papers.

Update: Here are some instructions if you want to create an RMarkdown document during the meetup:

- Install RStudio. That's it for the basics.

- To create an APA style article, then follow the instructions here: https://github.com/crsh/papaja

All materials and slides will be posted on github after the meetup and the link will be shared in the comments, as usual.

name: Introduction to ggplot2
description:
Sarah Hosking will provide an introduction to ggplot2. See below for more information.

Ggplot2 is one the go-to plotting libraries in R. One reason is in ggplot2 it's easy to quickly iterate plots, making it a great tool for exploratory data analysis (EDA).

This introductory session will take you through a visual EDA of a dataset using ggplot2. We will cover:

• Single-variable analysis with histograms, boxplots, scatterplots and line graphs

• Multiple-variable analysis through faceting, colour grouping, and correlation matrices.

If time allows, we can also look at creating and plotting summary statistics.

name: Manipuler et traiter les données manquantes dans R
description:
[événement en français animé par Julie Josse - http://juliejosse.com/]


Handling missing values in R,

The aim of this meetup is to present an overview of the missing values literature and to discuss the
potential pitfalls of the popular approaches in use and to show what are the recent tools available to
handle, in a practicable way, missing values.


We will touch upon the topics of single imputation with a focus on matrix completion methods
based on iterative regularized SVD, notions of confidence intervals by giving the fundamentals of
multiple imputation strategies, as well as issues of visualization with incomplete data.

The approaches will be illustrated with data with continuous, binary and categorical variables using
some of the main R packages Amelia, mice, missForest, missMDA, norm, softimpute, VIM.

Please download the dataset here : http://juliejosse.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/ozoneNA.csv
and be sure to have installed the packages below :


install.packages(c("VIM", "missMDA", "FactoMineR", "Amelia", "mice"))

name: Retour d'expérience : compétition Kaggle avec R
description:
Mercedes Sgobba, une de nos membres, nous a gentiment proposé de nous présenter son expérience d'utilisation de R dans le cadre d'une compétition Kaggle.

Il y a environ un an, le Groupe Bimbo a lancé une compétition Kaggle pour améliorer son activité.

Le Groupe Bimbo est la plus grande boulangerie au monde.

Description de la compétition :

Le Groupe Bimbo voudrait comprendre la consommation journalière de pain/produits de boulangerie au Mexique où les produits sont vendus dans les rayons de plus d’1 million de points de ventes.

A date, les commandes quotidiennes sont calculées à la main par le personnel de livraison. Certains de ces produits ont une ‘shelf life’ d’une semaine au max. Il s’agira développer un modèle de prévision de la demande.

Points clés : 74 millions d’observations, long travail de traitement de la donnée et jonction de plusieurs fichiers, élimination de duplicata, transformation en facteurs, ACP & Corrélation de variables, plusieurs exemples de visualisations avec R, découverte de fraude et construction d’un modèle de prévisions de la demande via un algorithme, comparaison de modèles (régression linaire, random forest..).

https://www.kaggle.com/c/grupo-bimbo-inventory-demand

name: #4 - Hands-on Shiny - Lets make your analysis interactive!
description:
Dear Ladies,

unbelievable R-Ladies Berlin turned 1! Thank you for all coming to our events and contributing to the great atmosphere and exciting discussions!

R's Shiny package allows you to conveniently build your own dashboards directly in your R scripts without any knowledge of web development. Have a look at the colourful online at shiny.rstudio.com.

Our guest speaker this week is Jakob Graff, a Data Scientist at Babbel and an R enthusiast. Based on examples, we will first cover the basics of Shiny. You will learn how dashboards with Shiny work, and get to know common building blocks.

In the second part of the session, we will go through a hands-on tutorial based on a simple example to get you started with Shiny.

In order to get all the output bring your laptop. Please, take care that you have working and updated version of the packages shiny and rmarkdown. 

We recommend checking out R-Studio's website, as they recently published a new version of R-Studio containing a number of nice features.


Drop us a message in case you have further questions. We are looking forward to meet up with you next week!

Cheers,

description:
Please join us for the R-Ladies Nashville Kickoff!

We'll provide some light snacks and beverages; if you'd like to bring dinner, feel free!

We'll meet in the VUMC Biostatistics large conference room, located on the 11th floor of the 2525 West End building (the building across from Centennial Park, with Barnes & Noble and PF Chang's on the ground floor). Paid parking is available in the garage behind the building, or some of the shops downstairs will validate for paying customers, if you'd like to come early.

name: December Meetup: data.table package
description:
Bring your lunch and join us for our first daytime meetup! JoAnn Rudd Alvarez will be teaching us about the data.table package (see abstract below). We'll again be meeting in the VUMC Department of Biostatistics conference room; there is paid parking available in the 2525 West End garage behind the building.

data.table: Where have you been all my life?

data.table is an easy to use R package for querying and manipulating data. Dataset updates run much faster than with the base R paradigm, and specifying complicated calculations is more intuitive. This talk will show some of the package's features as well as point out a couple of gotchas.

name: January Meetup: R Resources & Help
description: Have you had so-so luck Googling your R error messages? Want to learn Shiny but don't know where to start? Feel like you're behind the curve but don't know where to keep up with R news? This is the meetup for you! We'll talk about good sources for R news and updates, courses and tutorials, and tips on searching for topics and asking questions.

name: February Meetup: RStudio Conference Highlights!
description:
The RStudio Conference sounds like it was excellent, and we're all sad we missed out... but fortunately, a few of us WERE able to make it, and are bringing us back the highlights! We'll hear from Lucy, Alli & Jacquelyn about R-related news; developments with RMarkdown and reproducible research, new packages, Shiny and interactive graphics; and the most exciting ideas and tricks they picked up. Get excited by checking out the schedule and the Twitter buzz, then bring your lunch and join us! We expect there will be enthusiasm, fun photos, great ideas and possibly puns.

And if you see a talk in the schedule you're especially interested in, let us know so the ladies can make sure to tell us about it!

Parking tip: If you pick up lunch or a beverage from the shops downstairs, most will validate parking in the building's garage. There's Moe's, Bread & Co, PF Chang's and Starbucks to choose from.

Join us to learn about how you can make your own web app using just R code, led by Hannah Weeks. We’ll discuss the basics of Shiny and where to find additional resources, and also walk through a demo app. Come learn about some tips and tricks for getting started with Shiny!

Paid parking is available in the 2525 West End garage directly behind the building. Important: The conference room is on the 11th floor; elevators at 2525 are keycard access only after 6pm. Please let us know if you'll be arriving late, and we can give you contact information so someone can come downstairs to meet you.

• What is so great about GitHub?

• How can I make it work for me and my workflow?

• How can I show the world some of the cool things I’m working on?

This will be a hands-on workshop that will give you all the tools to have a delightful time incorporating version control & R (and blogdown if you are so inclined). All levels are welcome!

Stay 15 minutes after for a tour of the Wond’ry, part of Vanderbilt's new engineering facility! Parking is available in the 25th Avenue garage directly across Highland Avenue; see the Wond'ry page for more information. The building is also a <10-minute walk from both the 2525 West End and VUMC areas.

We'll have some light snacks... and R-Ladies stickers!

SPEAKING OF FUN: IT'S OUR BIRTHDAY! In honor of our one-year anniversary, we'll have light dinner and beverages, provided by our friends at the R Consortium, and a party vibe! RSVP by Friday to be counted for dinner.

GitHub is used by many teams for version control, collaboration on code, documentation, and so much else. But what happens when your files won't merge? How do pull requests work? There's no need to burn it to the ground and start again!

This workshop with give you a chance to get a little more comfortable with many of the thing Git and GitHub can do and make the whole process less scary.

name: Book Club: Dear Data
description:
Hello R-Ladies! 

We would like to start a book club series and we are starting with Dear Data, a book about how two women (Giorgia Lupi & Stefanie Posavec) shared data visualization and collection ideas over one year through post cards.The book is largely images of their post cards back and forth with some text interludes. 

The book is beautiful and would be a great addition to your library! You can also check it out from the local Austin library or you can view it as an e-book through the library, both free with your library card! 

Search for "Dear Data" here on the library website: https://austin.bibliocommons.com/search

Also available at BookPeople : http://www.bookpeople.com/

For the meetup we will: 

1) Start with chatting over coffee and/or beer

2) Briefly summarise the book 

3) Go through discussion questions 

4) Hear your thoughts on the book!

We will follow up as the date approaches with potential discussion questions.

Hope to see you there!

Come join us at our first R-Ladies #LdnOnt event! This event will feature a tutorial on RMarkdown</a>, led by Cortney Hanna (PhD candidate in HRS). All experience levels welcome to attend!

description:
Hello again!

We are incredibly excited to now be able to host our meet ups at UnLondon's community building downtown, which provides us a more accessible space beyond the walls of the university, as well as access to their awesome community. Our next meet up will be there on May 1st from 3:30 to 5:30 pm. 

We have two topics to present to you this time, led by two awesomewomen:

1) Intro to R: Rachael Smyth will be walking us through some basic introductory material in R and best practices of writing your R scripts.

2) Intro to version control with GitHub: Pauline Barmby will then demonstrate the ins and outs of version control using GitHub, which can be an incredibly useful way of keeping track of changes you make to your scripts (or other documents).

We'll head out for beers somewhere nearby after we've wrapped up (potentially Milo's? TBD!).

Please RSVP if you plan on attending so we have an idea of how many to expect. 

See you all soon! Feel free to post on the discussion board if you have any questions!

name: 2D and 3D Graphics in R!
description:
Olivia Daub will be presenting some fun tricks you'll need to know in order to make awesome 3D graphics in R! The session will begin with an review/overview of more basic plots in ggplot, then get into more advanced plots. 

What do I need to bring? 

• Ensure you have an updated version of XQuartz downloaded (you'll need this for the R packages used to generate the 3D plots)

• Install the following R packages by running this code in your R console: 

• install.packages(c("car","psych","scatterplot3d","Rcmdr","rgl","gvlma"))

As usual, we'll make our way to a nearby pub for some beer and food after the session.

See you then!

name: Real usecase of applying data science on real problem-Special guest: HeartInData
description:
Ready to jump into the real world with the skills of data science? Then, this is the right event for you. We are pleased to introduce our special guest HeartInData (https://www.heartindata.it/about-us/english-version/) for our next event. HeartInData is a group of data professionals based on Milan which is founded in 2016. They do data science for social good, also work with people and organizations to accomplish high social impact projects in unprofitable ways using cutting-edge technologies and data models.

They are going to share with us their experience of applying data science on a real business project. The goal of their projects was to help the company to understand its data better and find answers to specific problems. To achieve this they used various methods such as data integration, cleaning, handling missing values, data exploration, clustering, and churn analysis. So you will have the chance to see the complete journey of dealing with a real problem from the data till result delivery.

So hurry up, join us and don’t forget to spread the invitation to your friends too!

name: Beginner Statistic workshop in R
description:
Beginner Statistic workshop in R

Speaker: Navid Nobani

In this workshop you will learn what is statistics, how it can be useful for data analysis and why as a data scientist you need to learn it. The topics are fundamental concepts, and are focused on:

- What are variable types in data and how to deal with them


- How to measure variability and central tendency of data

- How to choose graphical presentation types based on types of variables


- Linear & regression modeling

Language: Examples & exercises will be in R

Prerequisites: Having laptop is not mandatory

Target Audience: Beginners level

Bio: Navid is a data scientist at Prometeon Tyre Group. He has a background in Industrial Engineering and is working in the data science field since 2015. He uses R and Python in his daily activities to solve business problems in the marketing area.


If you are interested, don’t hesitate to join us & spread the event to your friends too. We are looking forward to meet up with you!

name: Collaborative Data Science with Kaggle Kernels and Datasets
description:
RLadies Los Angeles and LA Women Who Code are excited to present


Collaborative Data Science with Kaggle Kernels and Datasets

by Megan Risdal

Code and data sharing in collaboration with others is integral to open data science. On Kaggle, the world’s largest online data science community, users use Kernels as a platform to share and execute reproducible code and Datasets to access, analyze, and maintain public data projects. Since the introduction of Kernels in 2015, users have written tens of thousand of kernels in R, Python, and Julia. And in the past year, users and organizations have published over 2,000 public datasets. Over this time, Kernels and Datasets have transformed how the data science community tackles machine learning problems, collaborates, and learns. In this talk, Megan Risdal uses community metrics and insights to share what Kernels and Datasets have taught Kaggle about collaborative data science. 

Megan is a Community Advocate and Data Scientist at Kaggle. She holds master’s degrees in linguistics from UCLA and North Carolina State University.

Where: Google Venice, 400 Hampton Drive, Venice 90291

(Note: Enter through the gate on Sunset here: https://goo.gl/QwgtQf).

When: Tuesday October 17th, 2017

6.00: Doors open, food and drinks served. 

7.00: Talk start. 

8.00: Talk end. 

Unfortunately parking will not be provided, but there are public parking lots close by.

Food and drinks will be provided. 

Bring photo ID - we cannot admit without it. Please do not attend if you are not on the list of registered attendees. 

Please be Googley, and if you’re not going to be able to attend, cancel so that someone else can attend instead.

name: fundamental concepts of R & reproducible R Markdown documents
description:
R-Ladies Manchester is ready to announce our first event! 

R-Ladies Manchester is part of a global initiative, R-Ladies Global, designed to improve the gender diversity of R users worldwide and in particular, to improve the participation and experience of women in the R community. As part of the initiative, R-Ladies Manchester will host a number of talks and workshops about the use of R. It doesn't matter if you never used R or if you are an R expert, R-Ladies Manchester welcomes anyone with an interest in R. The goal is to promote R, exchange knowledge and create an R community among women. We are fully inclusive and respectful of LGBT identities - our priority is to provide a safe community space for anyone identifying as female who is interested in and/or working with R.

We will begin our first workshop by reinforcing the foundations of your data analysis knowledge and R skills, and then move on to creating reproducible reports using R Markdown. The workshop starts with some warm-ups to get your brain in R-mode, and to make sure the basics are covered. Through a series of demonstrations and hands on exercises, you will learn some of the fundamental concepts of R: basic use of the R/RStudio console, inputting and importing different data types, record keeping, graphs etc. It concludes by showing how to create reproducible R Markdown documents. You might wish to bring your own laptop!  

To gain an insight in the members’ competence and interest in R, we kindly ask you to answer our short survey and to spread the word about our group.

We are on Tweeter: @RLadiesManchest and on GitHab: RLadiesManchester

We hope you will join us!

description:
Agenda: 


• 6:00pm -- Doors open and refreshments

We will talk about what makes R uniquely suitable for doing data science.

We’ll discuss the tools needed in a typical data science project, which will be illustrated in a small case study. We’ll exchange ideas on how we think about exploring data science and the best ways of communicating the results with the target audience.

We would love you to come and join us, bring a friend or two and share your thoughts and experiences when working on your every-day DS projects.

You don’t have to be an R user to come and join our discussion, as long as you have interest in learning, doing and getting to know more about data science and R.

name: CANCELED - Maps with ggplot2
description:
**THIS MEETING WILL BE RESCHEDULED FOR A FUTURE DATE.**

Amy Szczepanski will teach us about making maps with ggplot2!

We can take advantage of ggplot2's ability to plot points, lines, and polygons to draw maps without relying on specialized GIS tools. We will combine data from several sources to make a map showing major geographical features in San Diego, median property values per census tract, and the flight paths of planes departing San Diego International airport. The presentation will start by plotting points in the (x, y) plane with ggplot2 and will review the key features of this package. Next, we will use ggmap to easily put those points in context on a map. Finally, we will use shapefiles to color in regions in our maps.

All materials for the tutorial can be found here.

name: Introduction to Shiny Apps
description:
For our September meeting Katie Heineman will give us an introductory walk through of Shiny apps:

Shiny is a web development platform developed through R Studio that allows R users to make interactive interfaces for datasets manipulation and visualization. For the tutorial, I will walk the group through the creation of a simple shiny app using the R ladies dataset, and then demo several shiny apps I have created through my work in plant ecology.


Before coming please do the following:

1) Install R Studio (https://www.rstudio.com/). 
2) Install the 'shiny' package
3) Optional: Sign up for a *free* Shiny.io account so you can practice deploying a shareable webapp: http://www.shinyapps.io/


All scripts can be found on our GitHub account.

Come for R, Shiny, and snacks!

name: Come and meet the R-Ladies community in Cape Town
description:
Dear All,

Please join us for the very first meetup of the R-Ladies Cape Town chapter. R-Ladies is a worldwide organisation whose mission is to promote gender diversity in the R community. There are many other R-Ladies chapters in cities all around the world. As an organization R-Ladies is fully inclusive of trans women, genderqueer women and non-binary people who are significantly female-identified, and the same stands for R-Ladies Cape Town. Please have a look at the R-Ladies rules and guidelines. 

The idea for the Cape Town chapter of R-Ladies Global is to bring together women who work with R to get to know, support and learn from each other. The R community suffers from an underrepresentation of women in every role and area of participation. You absolutely do not need to be good at R to be a part of this community.

Here is a map link to the venue for the meetup. We are very happy that it is so close to public transport for people who rely on it. I know we will be meeting outside peak hours. If you have any safety concerns regarding getting to the station or getting home, please get in touch and we will find out if anyone with a car is going your way and can lift you.

There will be some drinks and snacks to fuel the conversation. We will say a few words to kick off but otherwise please just come along, be brave and chat to people :)

We really hope to see you there. Please feel free to get in touch if you have any questions.

All the best,

Theoni, Megan and Wiebke

Best,

Megan, Wiebke and Theoni

name: Datavis with ggplot2 // What R-Ladies get up to in Tbilisi, Georgia
description:
Two R-Ladies from out of town will be visiting Cape Town for a conference and they got in touch to meet the local community. 

Alessandra will talk about data visualisation with ggplot2 and Liili will talk about what it's like being part of R-Ladies, Tbilisi, Georgia. 

Hope to see many of you there! I think it'll be really interesting. We'll me meeting at Greenpoint Cowering.

Address:

Greenpoint Coworking3rd Floor, Foyer A, Sovereign Quay 40 Somerset Road Green Point. 

Parking:

On a Saturday, there will be a fair bit of street parking available along Green Point main road, especially in the area of the Gallows Hill traffic department, which is 1 block away from the venue. Otherwise, the building has R8/hr parking in it's courtyard (enter through the boom near Limnos Bakery).

Once on site, ring the intercom to get buzzed into the building. All guests must please sign in at the security desk in the lobby before taking the lift to the third floor. The elevator opens up straight onto the entrance to the coworking space, and the meetup will happen in the boardroom which is up the first set of internal stairs and straight on along the corridor.

Theoni and Megan

name: International Women's Day Potluck
description:
For International Women's Day, we will be hosting a potluck to get to know each other better! Bring your favorite dish to share! If you're not sure what to bring, follow our suggestions based on your last name: 

If your last name starts with:

A – F bring a main course (cooked chicken, casserole, etc.)

G – K bring a side dish (salad, rolls, etc.)

L – Q bring dessert (cookies, brownies, etc.)

R – Z  bring drinks (soda pop, bottled water, etc.)

The organizers will provided plates, utensils, napkins, and cups, but please bring your own serving utensils!

name: Let's get Git-ting!
description:
Does this image accurately portray your workflow?

If so, this workshop is for you! 

In this workshop we will learn how to use git, a collaborative version control software, and avoid the above situation. 

Version control is a system that records changes to a file or set of files over time so that you can recall specific versions later. We will start from the very basics of version control (collaborating with your past self) and work up to the skills necessary to contribute to an existing open source project (collaborating with other people). Effective collaboration and version control are essential for researchers to easily recover from the nasty snafus that we (or our collaborators) can get ourselves into through better file management. So, what are you waiting for? Let's get git-ting!

Pre-workshop Homework:

If you plan on attending this workshop, please do the following two things ahead of time: 

• Sign up for GitHub (http://github.com)

• Install SourceTree client for Git (https://www.sourcetreeapp.com/)

name: R-Ladies Ames Welcome (Back) Potluck!
description:
Welcome back R-Ladies Ames! 

We hope you are having a good start to your semester! We will be having a potluck as our first event this year to catch up and to meet new R-Ladies in the Ames area! We will provide the meat and everyone will bring a dish to pass or beverages according to how long they've been using R:

• 1 year or less? Bring crunchy snacks like trail mix or pretzels


• 1-2 years? Bring desserts like cookies or brownies


• 3-4 years? Bring salad of any variety: pasta, fruit, jello (we're in the Midwest, after all), actual salad, etc. 

• 5+ years? Bring beverages like soda/pop, water, juice, etc. 

Please RSVP at this link no later than September 25th: http://bit.ly/RLadiesAmesFall17 

See you then! 

Sam, Jacqueline, Tesia, and Jing

This is a weekly meeting hosted by R-Lady Audrey McCombs and Haldre Rogers in EEOB for folks interested in learning R and eating lunch together. Thanks to Audrey for extending this invitation to all of R-Ladies Ames! They meet from 12-1pm every Friday in Bessey Hall, room 334. 

Email Audrey at amccombs@iastate.edu for more information. If you're looking to present some cool R packages, how to wrestle with analysis issues, good coding practices, data management techniques, or anything else that you find interesting and helpful when working in R, let Audrey know! They'd love to host your presentation!

name: R-Ladies Tbilisi Launch
description:
8 დეკემბერს, 19:00 საათზე, ეკონომიკის სკოლა აისეტის (ISET) საკონფერენციო დარბაზში (ზანდუკელის ქ. #16, I სართული) ჩატარდება R-Ladies Tbilisi-ის გასაცნობი სახის შეხვედრა. ჩვენ დეტალურად გაგაცნობთ R-Ladies ინიციატივასა და მის ფარგლებში დადეგმილ აქტივობებს;  ასევე, თქვენთან ერთად გადმოვწერთ R-სა და R-Studio-ს, გავეცნობით R-ის საწყისებსა და მის რამდენიმე ბრძანებას.

გთხოვთ, თუ შესაძლებელია, თან იქონიოთ თქვენი ლეპტოპი. შეხვედრა წარიმართება ინგლისურ ენაზე, თუმცა საჭიროების შემთხვევაში, ხელმისაწვდომი იქნება ქართული თარგმანიც.

===================================================================

R-Ladies Tbilisi launch meeting will take place on December 8 in ISET (conference hall, 1st floor) at 16 Zandukeli str. It will last between 7-9.30 PM. We will introduce the background of R-Ladies initiative, discuss the activities of R-Ladies with you, download and install R and R-Studio together, and go through first basic commands in R. Please bring your laptops, if possible. The event will be in English, but Georgian translation will be provided for those who need it.

name: Reading and handling data
description:
შემდეგი შეხვედრა გაიმართება 13 დეკემბერს ISET-ში (ოთახი #5.2) საღამოს 7-დან 9 საათამდე. გავივლით R-ის სხვადასხვა ტიპის ბრძანებებს და ვისწავლით, როგორ წავიკითხოთ, შევქმნათ და ვმართოთ მონაცემები.

ვინც ვერ მოახერხეთ მოსვლა, პირველი შეხვედრის მასალები შეგიძლიათ იხილოთ მოცემულ ბმულზე:

https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi

გთხოვთ, შემდეგ შეხვედრამდე გადმოწეროთ და დააყენოთ R და RStudio თქვენს ლეპტოპებში. 

R-ის გადმოსაწერად (Windows-ისთვის) გამოიყენეთ ეს ბმული: https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/base/

R-ის გადმოსაწერად (Mac-ისთვის) გამოიყენეთ ეს ბმული: https://cran.r-project.org/bin/macosx/

RStudio-ს გადმოსაწერად გამოიყენეთ ეს ბმული: https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/

ასევე, შეგიძლიათ გაეცნოთ R-ის საბაზისო ფუნქციებს (თავი I) მოცემულ ბმულზე: 

http://tryr.codeschool.com/levels/1/challenges/2

==============================================================

The next meeting will take place on December 13, in ISET (room 5.2, 5th floor), between 7 - 9 PM. We will go through commands on how to read in, create and handle data in R.


Materials from the last meeting are here: https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi 


Please download and install R and RStudio on your laptops before the meeting starts. 

You can download R here (for Windows): https://cran.r-project.org/bin/windows/base/

Or here (for Mac): https://cran.r-project.org/bin/macosx/

You also need to download RStudio from here: https://www.rstudio.com/products/rstudio/download/

Please familiarize yourself with the basic R expressions from chapter 1 of codeschool: http://tryr.codeschool.com/levels/1/challenges/2 .

22-ში გავაგრძელებთ მონაცემთა მართვისთვის საჭირო ბრძანებების შესწავლას და შევეხებით მატრიცებს.


გასული შეხვედრების მასალები შეგიძლიათ იხილოთ შემდეგ ბმულზე:

https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi

გთხოვთ, გაეცნოთ მეორე თავს:

http://tryr.codeschool.com/levels/1/challenges/2

======================================================

The next meetings will take place on December 22 and 27, at ISET (16 Zandukeli str), room 5.2. We will go through some data handling commands and work with matrices on December 22. The meeting starts at 7 PM.

You can access the materials from the previous sessions here: https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi.

Please familiarise yourself with the R expressions from chapter 2 of codeschool: http://tryr.codeschool.com/levels/1/challenges/2 .

name: Exploring Caucasus Barometer 2015 using R
description:
Eric Barrett will host our next meetup.

We will use the haven library from RStudio to import an SPSS or STATA dataset. We will review what we have learnt of data types, dataframes, factors/levels, and more to explore the 2015 Caucasus Barometer by asking it questions. We might, should time permit, use ggplot2's basic quick plot syntax to visual some results and export the images.

Packages to install:


haven


ggplot2

Datasets to download:


2015 Caucasus Barometer and its codebook from

http://caucasusbarometer.org/en/downloads/

description:
ჩვენი შემდეგი შეხვედრა შედგება 9 თებერვალს, ეკონომიკის საერთაშორისო სკოლა ISET-ის 5.2 ოთახში 19:00 საათზე.სესიას გაუძღვება ბრაიან კუნსი სტოქჰოლმის უნივერსიტეტიდან. სესია შეეხება შემდეგ საკითხებს:1. Rvest-მონაცემთა დაყოფა2. Dplyr და Lubridate - მონაცემთა დალაგება, ცვლილება, რეკონსტრუქცია3. ggplot2 - მონაცემთა ვიზუალიზაცია.

=====================================================

We will meet again next Thursday, February 9 in room 5.2 at ISET starting from 7PM. Brian Kuns from the University of Stockholm will go through the following topics: 1) Rvest – scraping (html) data, 2) Dplyr and Lubridate – tidying and rearranging data, 3) ggplot2 – plotting data.

name: T-test!
description:
მოგესალმებით!ჩვენი მომდევნო სესია შედგება 23 თებერვალს ეკონომიკის საერთაშორისო სკოლა ISET- ის 5.2 ოთახში 19:00 ზე.

ამ სესიის განმავლობაში გავივლით t ტესტს და მისი გამოყენების რამდენიმე გზას R-ში, ასევე ვისწავლით ფუნქიცის წერის საწყისებს და უკვე დაწერილი ფუნქციების გამოყენებას საჯაროდ წვდომადი მონაცემთა ბაზების მაგალითზე. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Our next session is on February 23. In this session, we’ll go over how to write a student’s test in R, and in the process learn the basics of writing a function in R. In addition, we’ll go over a few types of t-tests for different circumstances, using already written t-test functions which R has. Moving from the formulas and a brief beer involved history of the t-test, we’ll go over a few applications in R using publicly available data sets.

We meet again at ISET in room 5.2 from 7pm.

name: Looping through data
description:
Looping is automating a multi-step process by organizing sequences of actions or ‘batch’ processes and by grouping the parts that need to be repeated. 


During this meetup Brian Kuns will cover looping (base-R) and "data-wrangling" using dplyr and tidyr. If there's time, we will make a graph or two using ggplot2. The data we will be using is farm yield data at a country level from FAOSTAT. We will go through the procedure of downloading CSV data, looking at this raw data to see how it should be "wrangled" or cleaned (which columns are unnecessary? do the columns need to be transposed? etc...).

name: String manipulation in R
description:
ამ შეხვედრაზე ჩვენ შევეხებით R-ში ტექსტურ მონაცემებთან მუშაობის ძირითად ასპექტებს. ჩვენ ყურადღებას გავამახვილებთ stringr პაკეტზე, რომელიც გამოიყენება ტექსტის თანამიმდევრულად და ეფექტურად დასამუშავებლად კოდირების გათვალისწინებით.

საჩვენებლად განვიხილავთ babynames პაკეტს, რომელიც მოიცავს ამერიკელი ბავშვების სახელებს 1880 წლიდან 2015 წლამდე. ჩვენ დავადგენთ სახელების ყველაზე პოპულარულ პირველ ასოს და სიდიდეს წლის მიხედვით. დამხმარე პაკეტებად გამოვიყენებთ dplyr-ს მონაცემებთან სამუშაოდ და ggplot2-ს ვიზუალიზაციისთვის. 

===========================================

In this session we will go through basics of string manipulation in R. We will concentrate on stringr package, which provides consistent, efficient and encoding-aware tools to work with character strings.

As a demonstration, we will deal with babynames package, which contains US children names from 1880 to 2015. We will find the most popular first letter and length of name for each year. As supportive packages we will rely on dplyr for data manipulation and on ggplot2 for visualization.

name: არჩევნების შედეგების პროგნოზირება/ Predicting Election Outcomes
description:
წინამდებარე შეხვედრის მიმდინარეობისას, ჩვენ ყურადღებას დავუთმობთ სხვადასხვა მეთოდებით საქართველოს 2012 და 2016 წლის საპარლამენტო არჩევნების შედეგების პროგნოზირებას. განვიხილავთ როგორც დეტერმინისტულ (ე.წ. გამოკითხვათა საშუალოების, მოძრავი საშუალოს და შეწონილი საშუალოს), ასევე ისეთ მიდგომებს, რომლებიც საშუალებას იძლევა, შევაფასოთ გაურკვევლობა (მაგ. ინტეგრირებული ავტორეგრესიული მოძრავი საშუალოს და დინამიურ ბაიესურ მოდელებს).
სამუშაოდ იქონიეთ შემდეგი ბიბლიოთეკები: curl, dplyr, DT, ggplot2, ggrepel, knitr, lubridate, mapproj, maps, mvtnorm, purrr, reshape2, rmarkdown, rstan, shinystan, stringr, tidyr, zoo, forecast. მონაცემები და რეპლიკაციის სკრიპტი განთავსდება შეხვედრის შესაბამის github-გვერდზე: https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi/tree/master/2017_06_05_election_polling
=============================
During this meeting, we will focus on predicting election results for 2012 and 2016 parliamentary elections. We will go through both deterministic (polling average, weighted and moving average) and those methods which take into consideration uncertainty (e.g. autoregressive integrated models and dynamic Bayesian models).
Please install following libraries on your machine: curl, dplyr, DT, ggplot2, ggrepel, knitr, lubridate, mapproj, maps, mvtnorm, purrr, reshape2, rmarkdown, rstan, shinystan, stringr, tidyr, zoo, forecast. Data and replication scripts will be uploaded to the corresponding Github page: During this meeting, we will focus on predicting election results for 2012 and 2016 parliamentary elections. We will go through both deterministic (polling average, weighted and moving average) and those methods which take into consideration uncertainty (e.g. autoregressive integrated models and dynamic Bayesian models).
Please install following libraries on your machine: curl, dplyr, DT, ggplot2, ggrepel, knitr, lubridate, mapproj, maps, mvtnorm, purrr, reshape2, rmarkdown, rstan, shinystan, stringr, tidyr, zoo, forecast. Data and replication scripts will be uploaded to the corresponding Github page: https://github.com/rladies/meetup-presentations_tbilisi/tree/master/2017_06_05_election_polling

name: Extracting information from Facebook
description:
ლევან ბჟალავა ისაუბრებს თუ როგორ გადმოვწეროთ ინფორმაცია ფეისბუქის საჯარო გვერდებიდან, განვსაზღვროთ გვერდის ყველაზე პოპულარული პოსტი (მოწონებები, კომენტარები, გაზიარებები), შევამოწმოთ ვინ მოიწონა ეს პოსტი და განვსაზღვროთ ტრენდი-რომელ პოსტებს აქვს უკეთესი შედეგი. ჩვენ ასევე ვისაუბრებთ როგორ მოვძებნოთ ფეისბუქის ჯგუფები და როგორ გადმოვწეროთ ჯგუფიდან პოსტების მონაცემები.
=======================
Levan Bzhalava will talk about how to extract information from Facebook public pages, identify the most popular post of the page (likes, comments, shares), check who liked the post, and implement trend analysis - which posts are doing well. He will show how to search Facebook group page and extract group page post data.

name: Time-series in R
description:
შეხვედრა შეეხება დროით მწკრივეს. დავიწყებთ საბაზო ოპერაციების გაკეთებით პროგრამაში. შემდეგ როგორც ტექნიკური ისე თეორიული განხილვებით უფრო ღრმად შევეხებით სტაციონარული მწკრივების ორ ძირითად ტიპს: ავტორეგრესიულ (AR) და მცურავი საშუალოს (MA) პროცესებს. ასევე, განვიხილავთ ჰოდრიკ-პრესკოტის ფილტრს, რომლის მეშვეობით ერთმანეთისგან გამოვყობთ დროითი მწკრივის ციკლურ და ტრენდულ კომპონენტებს. ვიმუშავებთ  R-სტუდიო-ს პროგრამაში. შეხვედრის პრაქტიკული ნაწილისთვის ძირითადად გამოვიყენებთ სიმულაციურ მონაცემებს. შეხვედრა საინტერესო იქნება დამწყებთათვისაც. დაგვჭირდება “mFilter”-ის დაინსტალირება R-სტუდიო-ში. 

შეხვედრას წარმართავს ნინო მელითაური, სამუშაო ენა იქნება ქართული.


==============================================


The meet-up will be about time series. We will begin by basic operations on time series in R-studio.  Then by technical as well as by theoretical discussion we will go further and (1) we will analyze the basic types of stationary time series: autoregressive (AR) and moving average (MA) processes and (2) we will discuss Hodrick-prescott filter, by which we will show how we can separate trend and cyclical components of the time series. We will use R-studio. As practical side, mainly we will work on simulated data. The meet-up will be suitable also for beginners.

We will need “mFilter” package to install.

This meetup is hosted by Nino Melitauri and it will be held in Georgian.

name: R-Ladies თბილისის ახალი სეზონი
description:
გაცნობითი ხასიათის შესავალი სემინარები სექტემბერსა და ოქტომბერში, შაბათ–კვირას ჩატარდება. ამ შეხვედრებზე გავეცნობით R-ს საფუძვლებს (პროგრამის ინსტალაცია, მონაცემთა ობიექტები და სტრუქტურა, სტატისტიკა, ვიზუალიზაცია). პრაქტიკული ნაწილისთვის თან იქონიეთ თქვენი ან საზიარო ლეპტოპი მეგობართან ერთად. გთხოვთ, მიუთითოთ, რომელ შაბათ–კვირას შეძლებთ სემინარზე დასწრებას (ორივე შეხვედრა იგივე პროგრამას მოიცავს, ასე რომ, გთხოვთ, მხოლოდ ერთისთვის გაიაროთ რეგისტრაცია).

რეგისტრაცია: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd6jZBQDdt35Hg2MgsanSjgBUFxrY4ZOxwULKuWMIgXOGhMJQ/viewform

===================================
Introductory workshops for real beginners will be organised on two weekends in September and October. These meetups will introduce the basics of R (installing, data objects and structures, statistics, visualisation). Please bring a laptop or share one with a friend for practical sessions. Please choose which weekend you will be able to participate (both contain the same information so you should sign up only for one).

Information and registration: https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSd6jZBQDdt35Hg2MgsanSjgBUFxrY4ZOxwULKuWMIgXOGhMJQ/viewform

name: rmarkdown for beginners
description:
ჩვენი მომდევნო შეხვედრა გაიმართება 4 ოქტომბერს, 2017. შეხვედრის მთავარი თემა არის rmarkdown-ის გამოყენება. შევქმნით ახალ პროექტს. მარტივი მაგალითების გამოყენებით ავაგებთ rmarkdown-ის ფაილებს Rstudio-ს პროგრამაში. შევქმნით ახალ notebook-ს და ვისწავლით მის გამოყენებას. knit ბრძანებით ვნახავთ როგორ უნდა შევქმნათ ახალი ვორდის დოკუმენტი და ახალი პრეზენტაცია, რომლებშიც მოსახერხებელი გზით იქნება წარმოჩენილი ჩვენს მიერ ჩატარებული მარტივი ანალიზის სრული სურათი. შედეგების PDFფორმატში გამოსატანად შესაძლოა დაგვჭირდეს Latex-ის პროგრამა. (Latex-ის საინსტალაციო ლინკი: http://latex-project.org/ftp.html).

===================================

Our next meet-up will take place on October 4, 2017. The topic will be rmarkdown. We will begin by creating a new project, then using simple examples we will see how to build rmarkdown files in Rstudio. We will create a new notebook and see how it works. By using knit order we will produce a new word document and we will create a new presentation, showing conducted analysis in a convenient way. Also we will be able to have our output in PDF format, for this purpose you may need a Latex program (LaTeX installation link: http://latex-project.org/ftp.html).

The meetup will be hosted by Nino Melitauri in Georgian.

name: Shiny!
description:
Shiny არის პაკეტი რომელიც შესაძლებელია გამოვიყენოთ ინტერაქტიული ვებ გვერდების შესაქმნელად R studio-ში. სოფო რუხაძე გაგაცნობთ Shiny ფუნქციას და როგორ ხდება მისი გამოყენება R studio-ში გარკვეულ მონაცემებზე დაყრდნობით. შეხვედრა ჩატარდება ქართულ ენაზე.

==================================

Shiny is a package that can be used to build interactive web pages with R and RStudio. Sopho Rukhadze will introduce basic Shiny functions and how to build a Shiny app, using in-built data from R. The meetup will be in Georgian language.

name: Basics of machine learning with R
description:
The meetup is hosted by Vincenzo Lagani, post-doc researcher at the University of Crete and co-founder of Gnosis Data Analysis. His main research interest is devising machine learning and statistical algorithms, and their applications on a variety of fields, including biology, clinical and business data.
The meetup will focus on predictive analytics (classification), decision tree learners and neural networks (deep learning).
The talk will last ~90 minutes, during which Vincenzo will also show how to analyze a dataset in R.
After that the attendees should have ~30 minutes to repeat the analysis on a second dataset.
Approximate outline of the meetup:
1) Data mining, machine learning and statistics: putting concepts into context
2) Overview of machine learning tasks: classification, clustering, feature selection, association rules, etc.
3) Focus on classification: decision trees and neural networks
4) The importance of being honest: avoid overfitting at all costs!
5) Analyzing the MNIST dataset with decision trees and neural networks in R
6) Hands-on: analyzing the Iris dataset

================================

შეხვედრას უმასპინძლებს ვინჩენცო ლაგანი, რომელიც ისაუბრებს Machine learning-ზე. შეხვედრა ჩატარდება ინგლისურ ენაზე.

name: სტატისტიკური ანალიზი
description:
27 ოქტომბრის შეხვედრა კვლავ დაეთმობა სტატისტიკურ ანალიზს. კერძოდ, გავაგრძელებთ საუბარს ფიქტიურ ცვლადებსა და ინტერაქციულ წევრებზე წრფივ რეგრესიულ მოდელში. ზოგადი მიმოხილვის შემდეგ, ვიმუშავებთ პრაქტიკულ მაგალითზე, რომლის ფარგლებში გვექნება წინა შეხვედრის სტატისტიკური თემების გახსენებაც. შეხვედრის სამუშაო ენა იქნება ქართული.

====================================

This meetup will be a continuation of beginners' workshop's statistical analysis presentation. In particular, we will discuss dummy variables in linear models and interaction terms. After the general discussion we will work on a practical example. In addition, during the practical part, we will have a revision of the previous meetup's statistical topics. The meetup will be in Georgian.

name: Creating an R package
description:
The possibility of organizing code in packages is one of the main advantages of R. Packages can also be made publicly available so that everybody can benefit from them. This talk will show step-by-step how to create an R package from scratch, using a hands-on example.

Read about R packages here: https://www.statmethods.net/interface/packages.html

Vincenzo Lagani is hosting this meetup, in English.

===========================
R-ს ერთ-ერთი მთავარი უპირატესობა არის კოდების ორგანიზება პაკეტებში.  ეს პაკეტები შესაძლოა ასევე გახდეს საჯარო, რაც მათ ყველასთვის ხელმისაწვდომსა და სარგებლის მომტანს გახდის. ამ შეხვედრაზე გავიგებთ თუ როგორ შევქმნათ პაკეტები R-ში საწყისი დონიდან, პრაქტიკული მაგალითების საშუალებით.

name: Launch Meetup
description:
Hello Everyone,

Thanks for joining R-Ladies! We're excited to have you aboard.

Our Launch Meetup will be August 8th, 2017 , 7:00-8:30 PM at the Iron Yard. 

This is an opportunity for us to get to know each other, interact and mingle.  Every R level is welcome. If you don't know anything about R programming, but have been hearing about data analysis and data science , this is a great way to start. In this meeting we will help you install R, Rstudio and Github, so that you can be ready to tackle the projects and tutorials coming the next meetups.

If you are an R expert, please join our chapter  and the launch meeting, as you can help better serve our community by setting goals and priorities for our chapter. All of us, at any level of expertise will help shape the goals and direction of this chapter; so please join us!

We hope this will be a collaborative, supportive space to get to know other folks doing work in R, hear about interesting projects, and find your community and collaborators.


Check out our website  to learn more about R-Ladies and here is our code of conduct

The tentative agenda includes: 

7:00 PM - 7:30 PM - Arrive & Enjoy snacks and drinks

7:30 PM - 8:00 PM -  Short presentation & discussion 


       • Intro to R-Ladies

       • What is R? why do I need it?

       • Open discussion for future Meetup ideas! 

8:00 PM - 8:30 PM - Install R, R Studio and Github.

Please RSVP so that I can plan seating, food and raffle prizes.

Again, thank you for your support and looking forward to meeting you all.

And special thank you to the  Iron Yard for giving us a space to use.

Kathy

name: Introduction to R ( Part of Beginners R Workshops)
description:
Introduction to R and RStudio

R-Ladies Orlando will be running few sessions for Absolute R Beginners!! There will be a short intro to RStudio and R basics at 7:00,  followed by Q&A time. This is an opportunity for anyone completely new to R to get started.

Bring your (charged) laptop and we'll help you get up and running with the software, walk you through the R programming basics, help with FAQs, point you to relevant learning resources, and any other fundamental R questions you may have!

Please make sure you have R and RStudio downloaded ready to go. 

To download R, go to https://cloud.r-project.org 

To download RStudio http://www.rstudio.com/download

Follow the instructions to download and install. 

Also please create an account with Kaggle, as we are going to be using a lot of their datasets. I think you can loggin with your gmail, yahoo and even facebook account.

After we get comfortable playing with R and RStudio will start a series of workshops that will be based on Garrett Grolemund and Hadley Wickham book, "R for Data Science" http://r4ds.had.co.nz/

* Visualization: Base R + ggplot 

* Introduction to tidyverse

name: Primer Meetup de RLadies Montevideo!
description:
Hola a tod@s!

Estamos muy contentas de anunciar nuestro primer evento en Montevideo! 

Nuestras speakers:

Carolina Crisci es bióloga de formación. Fue Ayudante por algunos años en el Laboratorio de Probabilidad y Estadística del Instituto de Matemática en la Facultad de Ingeniería donde comenzó a trabajar en la aplicación de modelización estadística a problemas biológicos. Siempre con la perspectiva de combinar la Biología y la Estadística, se formó como Doctora en Oceanografía en la Université de la Méditerranée (Francia) y al volver a Uruguay realizó un postdoc en el área de Ecología Acuática. Actualmente es Profesora Adjunta en el Centro Universitario Regional del Este (Rocha), donde forma parte del grupo Modelización y Análisis de Recursos Naturales.

María Eugenia Riaño es docente del Departamento de Métodos Cuantitativos de la Facultad de Ciencias Económicas. Trabaja en el área de Muestreo, y ha participado de varios proyectos vinculados al área. También trabajó en el Instituto Nacional de Estadística, encargándose del muestra de la Encuesta Continua de Hogares. Sus intereses son muestreo y estadística espacial.

Natalia Berberian y Alejandra Borges. Natalia es Licenciada en Estadística y Magíster en Ciencias Agrarias, Opción Bioestadística. Trabaja en el Departamento de Biometría, Estadística y Computación de la Facultad de Agronomía desde 2010. Se involucró en el uso de modelos espaciales en el contexto de diseño de experimentos en su tesis de Maestría. Alejandra es Ingeniera Agrónoma y Magíster en Ciencias Agrarias, Opción Ciencias Vegetales. Actualmente está realizando un Doctorado en Ciencias Agrarias. Trabaja en el Departamento de Biometría, Estadística y Computación de la Facultad de Agronomía desde 2006. Se involucró en el uso de modelos espaciales en el contexto de diseño de experimentos en su tesis de Doctorado y en diversos proyectos de investigación. Actualmente dictan un curso de posgrado en la Maestría en Ciencias Agrarias de Introducción a la Geoestadística que se ofrece cada dos años en Facultad de Agronomía.

Agenda:

19:00 - 19:20 networking 

19:20 – 19:40 Natalia y Daniela (organizadoras) presentan “Qué es R-Ladies y por qué existe?”

20:25 – 20:40 Natalia y Alejandra presentan “Modelos espaciales en el contexto de diseño de experimentos”

name: R-Ladies PDX First Meetup
description:
We're finally kicking off our first R-Ladies PDX Meetup!

Apologies for the short notice on this but rest assured there will be more meetups in the near future if you can't make this one. The goal of this Meetup is really just to start the momentum and get the group going!

Our meeting space is a conference room located in the WeWork office that has restricted public access. We have the space reserved starting at 6pm, so feel free to come a little early! 

UPDATE: We will have food: Tacos from Uno Mas (http://unomastaquiza.com/ - vegetarian + GF options) and non-alcoholic beverages!

Here is the suggested agenda, times may shift depending on how many folks show up and what people are interested in sharing.

6:30 - Introductions

•  What is R-Ladies?

• What would we all like to get out of R-Ladies PDX? 

• Any other R-Ladies items folks want to discuss, feel free to add to the doc (R-Ladies Agenda Items) or contact Augustina or Deeksha.

You can also use comments in this event for your suggestions. If we run short of time, we can continue the discussion online and at a future meetup! 

7:00 - Lightning talks

Around 5-10 minutes each - topic: "Something I currently do or want to do with R"

This is a very informal opportunity for anyone who wants to share something they are excited about or just wants to get more comfortable talking in front of others in a friendly space. You don't have to have slides or anything fancy! Sign up here (Lightning Talks Sign Up) or message Augustina or Deeksha!

7:30 - Wrap up! 

Many thanks to Chester Ismay and WeWork for hosting our first Meetup!


Also thanks to IBM for sponsoring the food!

name: Text Mining with Tidy Data Principles with Julia Silge
description:
Co-hosted event with Portland Data Science and Portland R Users Meetups!

Julia Silge is gracing PDX with her presence and has offered to share her knowledge on Tidy Text Mining Principles! Julia is based out of Salt Lake City, Utah and currently works for Stack Overflow as a Data Scientist. She is also co-author of the book "Text Mining with R" available here - http://tidytextmining.com/

Abstract:

Unstructured, text-heavy data sets are increasingly important in many domains, and tidy data principles and tidy tools can make text mining easier and more effective. In this talk, I will demonstrate how we can manipulate, summarize, and visualize the characteristics of text using R packages from the tidy tool ecosystem; these tools extend naturally to many text analyses and allow analysts to integrate natural language processing into effective workflows already in wide use. We will explore how to implement approaches such as sentiment analysis of texts and measuring tf-idf to quantify what a document is about.

IBM is sponsoring food + drinks! We will have hearty appetizers from Elephant's Delicatessen (w/ vegetarian and GF options) and a small selection of beer, wine, and non-alcoholic beverages.

name: Welcome to R-Ladies Montenegro!
description:
R-Ladies Montenegro is happy to announce our 1st MeetUp for 25 August 2017 at 19:00 in Herceg Novi (Caffe Bar Porto).

If you would like to learn R and share your experience of working in R or would just like to find out what is R this would be a perfect place for you. It doesn't matter whether you are a beginner or an experienced R coder, come and join us! 

In our first meeting we will talk about why R is language of choice for many data scientists through a series of demonstrations and hands on exercises. You will be able to learn some of the fundamental concepts of R: basic use of R/RStudio console, inputting and importing different data types, record keeping, graphs etc. We will conclude our first meeting by showing how to create reproducible R-Markdown documents. If you have a laptop bring it with you so we can do some R coding together. We will show you how to install R and RStudio if you haven’t already done so.

If any of you would like to present short demos of R code you are using in your projects or R packages please get in touch and we will include it in our programme.

The final programme will be announced a few days prior to the meeting.

We are looking forward to seeing you all…

> #---------------------------------------------------------------------

R-Ladies Montenegro sa zadovoljstvom najavljuju naš prvi MeetUp 25. avgusta 2017. u 19h u Herceg Novom (Caffe Bar Porto).

Ako želite naučiti R, podeliti svoje iskustvo u korišćenju R-a, ili biste samo želeli saznati što je to R, ovo će biti savršeno mesto za vas. Nije važno da li ste početnik ili iskusan R koder, dođite i pridružite nam se!

Na našem prvom sastanku razgovaraćemo o tome zašto je jezik R izbor za mnoge data scientist-e kroz niz demonstracija i konkretnih vežbi. Moći ćete naučiti neke od osnovnih pojmova R-a, osnovnu upotrebu R/RStudio programa: unos i snimanje različitih vrsta podataka, grafički prikaz itd. Završi ćemo naš prvi sastanak tako što ćemo prikazati kako kreirati reproducibilni R-Markdown dokument. Ako imate laptop, donesite ga tako da možemo R-kodirati zajedno. Ako nemate R i RStudio na svom kompjuteru, pomoći ćemo vam da ih instalirate.

Ako neko od vas želi demonstrirati svoj projekat i kod u R-u, ili svoj R-paket, molimo da nas kontaktirate kako bi smo vas uključili u programsku šemu.

Konačna programska šema biće objavljena nekoliko dana pre sastanka.

Unapred se radujemo našem susretu…

name: Presentación de R-Ladies y Aplicaciones de R en Santa Rosa
description:
El ITES nos invitó a dar una charla para los estudiantes de la Tecnicatura Superior en Desarrollo de Software y al público en general este jueves 22 de junio a partir de las 21:30 hs.

Las disertantes son la Magister en Explotación de Datos y Gestión de Conocimiento, Investigadora del INTA, Yanina Bellini Saibene y la Estudiante de Doctorado en Ciencias Agrarias de la UBA Marina Cook ambas organizadoras de RLadies Santa Rosa. En primer lugar se expondrá sobre Agro Minería de Datos: en un mundo que necesita cada vez mas alimentos, producir más y mejor, cuidando la salud y el medio ambiente, es uno de los desafíos del sector agropecuario. La minería de datos es una de las herramientas que puede ayudar en este objetivo al permitir analizar y modelar los sistemas productivos. Se informará sobre el uso de Data Mining en INTA y como R les ayuda en esa tarea.


En la segunda parte se referirán a Modelos Mixtos: los avances en informática permitieron desarrollar modelos más complejos y realistas para el análisis de datos. Nos mostrarán qué modelos usan y por qué; por qué usar R y que ventajas ofrece.

Finalmente se hablará sobre RLadies: presentaremos el capitulo Santa Rosa de esta organización mundial que busca disminuir la brecha de género en las personas que usan R.


Los espermos!!!

name: [Education Series] 擁抱跨界力 – CS+X 的新方向 p.s. Working With JavaScript In R
description:
[Agenda]


• 19:15-19:30 R Basic

• 19:30-20:30 主議程: 擁抱跨界力 – CS+X 的新方向 p.s. Working With JavaScript In R @Pecu

• 20:30-20:50 閃電秀:  Power BI with R @Kristen

• 20:50 -  自由交流時間

[Talk Information]

• 擁抱跨界力 - CS+X 的新方向 p.s. Working With JavaScript In R
寫程式、訓練計算思維(Computational Thinking)全球都在瘋。程式語言儼然已成為全民必修的第二外語。我們想透過本次分享來探討， 程式語言在歷史、中文、新聞、生活與個人價值 到底發生了何種巨大的影響力？

本次分享目標在滿足三種需求：

1. 了解寫程式的重要，但是不知道如何開始？

2. 已經開始接觸一段時間卻遇到瓶頸，但不知道如何重拾熱情？

3. 已經是神人等級的高手，但卻不知道該如何觀察身邊的問題？


最後，用Working With JavaScript In R的 Living Coding來結尾，期待，共同創造更多擁有跨領域人才。

• Power BI with R
Power BI 是微軟推出非常好用的BI工具，也支援了多種的來源 Excel, Microsoft SQL, JSON, Microsoft Azure....

description:

19:30-20:00 Lightening Talk 閃電秀
An (Short?) Introduction to Bioconda, UpSetR, and snakemake 
@亮亮 liang2

20:00-21:00 Main Session 主議程
Harnessing social media data with machine learning 
@Lucia


•Main Session 主議程

Title: Harnessing social media data with machine learning 

Abstract: Judging others' psychological traits is not only an essential skill in successful social living, but also an important factor in product development. Psychological traits are a key driver behind human interaction, behavior and emotions. Although accurate judgments stem from social-cognitive skills, developments in machine learning show that computer models can also make valid judgments. It is also possible that this technique can assist clinical diagnosis in the future.

Research by Lucia Chen (speaking), Tao Gong and Rob Davidson.
Directions: https://m-labs.hk/public_events.html 

• Speaker: Lucia, Lushi Chen

Master in Linguistics  The University of Hong KongMaster in Psychology City University of Hong Kong 
Lucia has just finished her master degree of psychology this December. She is going to pursue a doctoral degree in psychology in the coming year.Her major research area is to use social media data to predict psychological traits. Her previous works include using internet data to predict user’s satisfaction with life and depression symptoms.She is also interested in app development, especially a chat bot.
Programming language: R, Python, Javascript, HTML, Meteor Actual speaking language: Chinese, English and some broken Japanese

Interests: watch panda videos on ipanda, foodie, traveling

• Lightening Talk 閃電秀

Title: An (Short) Introduction to Bioconda, UpSetR, and snakemake

Abstract: This short talk will introduce a few interesting on-going R projects and packages in independent sections.  First section covers (Bio)conda, the package management system for both R and Python, where bioconda brings sepecific support for commonly used bioinformatic tools in both languages.  Second section introduces a R package, UpSetR, which implements a novel way to visualize intersections of sets, that is, to visualize how different groups of samples overlap with each other.  If time permits, lastly, an extended makefile-like build system, snakemake, will be demonstrated to construct a parallelized analysis pipeline involving both R and Python scripts.

Speaker: 亮亮 (or liang2), Liang-Bo Wang

亮亮 (or liang2) is a PhD student in Computational and Systems Biology at Washington University in St. Louis (WUSTL) with research interest in cancer genomics. Aside from academics, liang2 attends and speaks in Python and R open source communities, including Taipei.py and MLDM Monday. His recent project is the Chinese translation of the official Python documentation.

description:
[Agenda]

• 20:50 - 自由交流時間

[Talk Information]

• Shiny apps on Azure

想把做好的圖表分享給其他人? 想要有個互動的網頁來呈現R跑出來的成果?利用Shiny和Azure可以快速的完成喔!這次會先簡單的介紹Shiny和Azure，並會用一個範例帶大家實作。

Do you want to share with others the analytic project you work on? Do you want to build an interactive web page to show the result? With Shiny and Azure, you can make it easily and quickly. This time we will introduce Shiny and Azure first, and then demo with an example.

• 翻玩空氣盒子--監控空氣品質

Location Aware Sensing System (LASS)社群，是由對環境感測有興趣的Makers, Contributors組成。目前主要專注在pm2.5的空氣污染監測。其使用低成本、體積小、高準確度的微型感測器, 達到可大量、高密度部署的目標。去年更結合政府、民間企業和社群力量，推出空氣盒子, 目前於台北市各小學校皆有部點, 下半年更推廣到5都, 希望喚醒群眾對空氣污染議題的關注。將介紹利用其open data目前做到的分析情形。希望越多人加入一起關心空汙的感測。

LASS Community, consisted of makers/contributors interested in environment sensing, focuses on air pollution issues. Last year they started to apply air boxs as micro sensors for pm 2.5. This time we will show the analysis of open data collected by the air boxes. Join us on the air pollution issues.

[Speaker Information]

• Kristen
喜歡學任何新鮮有趣的東西，看到 R Ladies 大家無私地分享很多知識給大家，很期望也能貢獻一點自己學到的東西，並與大家一同成長。

目前任職於研究單位，熱於參加各種社群，從中學習互相交流，喜歡大家下班還能聚在一起學習的感覺，希望能將所學知識和大家分享。

description:

[Talk Information]

•  Azure ML  
不會寫程式是否也能預測新發單曲是否賣座[Azure及R的教學] 

每張新唱片問世，都需唱片公司投入大量預算，如何能預測單曲是否暢銷變成關鍵。透過MIT/edX Popularity of Music Records課程的資料集，收集了1990-2010告示牌排行榜前十大及非前十大單曲，透過Logistic Regression來建立模型。

此次talk嘗試透過Azure讓不會寫程式的人也能建立自己的模型，也分享R + Azure有甚麼好用的小地方。


•Azure Machine Learning - Feature Engineering                   

被喻為是“Data scientist's Secret Sauce!”的Feature Engineering(特徵工程)，到底是有什麼樣的魔力，讓大家對他有這個稱號。

在資料分析和建模當中，要透過什麼方式，把現實生活當中的情境透過feature描述，轉化成model裡面相對應的數值？

如果你心中有些想要透過machine learning解決的問題，也對該問題有一些相對應的domain knowhow，卻不知道應該在哪裡把自己的知識加進去訓練模型的步驟裡，也許你會從這次的分享有一些收穫。

或是你已經嘗試了一些演算法，想知道在Data 跟 Model 之間的轉換到底是有哪些秘方讓自己的模型可以更fit 自己遇到的問題，也許你會從這次的分享帶給你一些新的靈感在你分析的流程上。

[Speaker Information]

• Ning
熱愛作資料解讀及分析，共同創立 TW R Ladies，曾經在網路公司做過分析師．希望能認識更多同好，一起做好玩且不一樣的事情。


• 懷文 
喜歡從資料當中找出一些現象，從中和現實生活當中的問題互動。在一些不同的新創專案當中擔任資料顧問，也是Azure Taiwan社群的共同創辦人，希望和大家多認識，聽聽大家對身邊資料集的不同想像。

昱璇 Dana

資料新聞及資料視覺化，一般是將各種數據作為新聞或者論述的作證，以表格、圖表，甚至更多元的互動方式，來達到讓讀者更快速、更深入理解議題的效果。這次會介紹國內外精彩的資料新聞案例，也簡單分享我製作中的一些思考。

[Talk Information]

•  RBasic  

 RLadies RBasic 小組的 RBasic 系列

• Digital Humanities in R 

甚麼是數位人文？我在德國的做的研究是甚麼？如何使用 R 於數位人文的領域上


•  媽，我交了個大象朋友

在這一場分享裡，聖佑試著回顧當初接觸 PHP 程式語言的過程，並透過擬人化的方式將 PHP 的吉祥物「大象」比擬成自己在小時候交的一位朋友。以介紹朋友的方式，期望能在 15 分鐘超短的時間內，讓完全不認識 PHP 這個程式語言的朋友能對它有初步的認識，並能試著開始撰寫自己的第一個 PHP 網頁


•  如何快速尋出有問題的入侵記錄
網站攻防已然是目前資訊安全領域的顯學，但對於一個服務提供者而言，最重要的是忠實的呈現客戶發生了什麼事情，因此在LOG的分析上是一個相當重要的工作，透過各種不同的方法快速的顯示出有問題的記錄，免除了過多的人為主觀，透過分析的過程找出切入點，及真的的根本原因才是最終的目標


[Speaker Information]

• 蔡芸琤(Pecu) 
目前在大學擔任菜鳥老師，負責 CS+X 推廣與教學工作，兩年前有機會到德國某研究中心工作，接觸到了數位人文的研究議題，深深喜歡上文理一家融合的思考方式，大大推翻台灣在高中就將文理組分家的教育方式，因此，想在台灣進行跨領域教育推廣工作，希望能聚集喜歡實踐想法的人們，一起改變世界

•  范聖佑 (Shengyou Fan)

現職為得寬科技研究員、Laravel 傳教士。2013 年在 Facebook 上成立 Laravel 台灣 社團及成立 Laravel 道場 教學站，並與多間學校、企業單位合作舉辦教育訓練工作坊，從此踏上 Laravel 傳教與導入之路。除此之外也在 Github 上發佈數項與 Laravel 開發相關的懶人包與外掛，每個月固定舉辦三場 PHP/Laravel 活動，以實現簡潔優雅開發為夢想。持續關注創新應用、網路技術、印刷出版及甜點烘焙等領域。目前抱著甜點書持續 Full Stack 的旅程！


• 黃建笙


登豐數位科技技術總監，專長為windows安全、web安全及資訊安全事件鑑識，具有CISSP-ISSMP, CEH, CHFI, ECSA, ISO27001LA,BS10012LA等資訊安全相關認證，我就是因為懶所以懂得如何讓工作自動化，也因為懶所以常用各種新的方法來讓工作更有效率，在入侵事件中最重要的一環是log分析，透過各種不同的方法快速的找出有問題的記錄，減少目前的工作負載，讓更多的時間可以用在維護世界和平上。


[Host information]

• Rachael

name: [Security Series] 資安與 R
description:
[Agenda] 

• 19:15-19:30 R Basic @Vivian, Dana, 謝包妹

• 19:30-20:30 主議程: 如何以R做為事件蒐集及分析的利器 @方丈

• 20:30-20:50 閃電秀:  dplyr 介紹 @王斯霈

• 20:50-21:00 閃電秀: R-Ladies Taipei Kaggle大賽小小心得分享 @Kristen


• 21:00 -  自由交流時間


[Talk Information]

• 如何以R做為事件蒐集及分析的利器

資訊安全事件層出不窮，在第一線的LOG蒐集即是一件需要大量投入資源的工作，而往後的事件分析及事件追縱是另一個管理問題。單就事件分析及關聯性，R是一個非常好的工具及平台。接承前一次閃電秀中說明的事件發生的始末，本次議程深入的探討如何以R來挖掘入侵事件，進而建置一個屬於自已的事件偵測機制。

• dplyr 介紹


如何迅速將資料調處到理想的樣子在資料進到模型進行分析之前有好長一段路要走，那就是-資料調處。我們將在20分鐘內體驗資料整理的辛酸，體驗資料分析90%的時間所做的事情吧!

•  R-Ladies Taipei Kaggle大賽小小心得分享

你有玩過Kaggle嗎？你想玩Kaggle但來不及參加R-Ladies Taipei 2017 Kaggle 大賽？沒關係！你可以來聽聽這次 R-Ladies Taipei 2017 Kaggle 大賽選定的題目、助教攤常見問題、以及為何參賽者們都需要 Azure 的幫助 ?! 或許聽完後你也會開始挑戰你的第一場Kaggle比賽。

[Speaker Information]

• 方丈
登豐數位科技技術總監，專長為windows安全、web安全及資訊安全事件鑑識，具有CISSP-ISSMP, CEH, CHFI, ECSA, ISO27001LA,BS10012LA等資訊安全相關認證，我就是因為懶所以懂得如何讓工作自動化，也因為懶所以常用各種新的方法來讓工作更有效率，在入侵事件中最重要的一環是log分析，透過各種不同的方法快速的找出有問題的記錄，減少目前的工作負載，讓更多的時間可以用在維護世界和平上。

•  王斯霈
王斯霈勤業眾信聯合會計師事務所風險管理部門數據分析，腦袋想不開從統計系轉到資訊管理所就讀，從此踏上STAT+IT的生活。是個剛出社會的新鮮人，期望能持續朝資料科學家邁進。 

•  Kristen Chan
目前在Wave-In擔任資料科學家，專長是電子商務數據挖掘和電信數據分析。她樂於與 R-Ladies Taipei 的夥伴分享經驗和知識，並希望透過 R-Ladies Taipei 讓更多女性朋友不再害怕 Coding，並了解數據分析其中的奧妙。現在也是 R-Ladies Taipei Officer 之一。現任微軟 MVP 最有價值專家。

[Host information]

• Yen

name: [女力 x 資料科學 x 數據應用] Joint Meetup with PyLadies and Girls in Tech
description:
# 本活動由國泰金控贊助下午茶

# 本活動由台灣微軟贊助場地

# 本活動報名截止於 8/6, 上限 70 人，免費~
# R-Ladies/ PyLadies/ Girls in Tech 擇一報名就可以囉
# 只限女生報名喔

這是 R-Ladies, Girls in Tech, PyLadies 首次合辦的講座活動，議程將環繞著我們的主題「女力 x 資料科學 x 數據應用」！延續過去每個月的技術講座，除了一樣著重在資料應用案例分享外，這次跨社群的橫向交流也是一大重點。讓我們期待 3 個性質各異的女性社群可以激盪出什麼火花，也期待更多未來的合作！

Agenda

13:30 [社群介紹]
Girls in Tech、R-Ladies、PyLadies

13:45 [女力講座]
女性社群力量@Angie & Yi-chu (Girls in Tech)

14:15 [社群交流時間]

15:15 [下午茶茶歇]

15:30 [資料科學講座]
用 R 玩 Kaggle – 臉書打卡點預測 @Mia (R-Ladies)

16:00 [數據應用講座]
如何用數據打造最貼心的旅遊搜尋引擎@Mars (PyLadies)

16:30
Open Mic/擺攤

Abstract

• 女性社群力量
Angie將分享她如何從商管跨入數據分析領域，在男女比1:5的團隊遇到哪些困難，又從社群看到什麼學到什麼~


• 用Ｒ玩 Kaggle: 預測臉書打卡點
Kaggle是資料科學們最常出沒的線上資料競賽平台，在上面除了有open data 可以使用，也可以透過參加競賽練習自己的能力。這場分享將會快速帶大家用 R 玩Kaggle，挑戰2016年Facebook在網站上公開的資料，預測下一個熱門的打卡點會是在哪裡～學習如何思考問題跟解決問題！

• 如何用數據打造最貼心的旅遊搜尋引擎
旅行是一個非常有趣的議題，背後是由極為複雜資訊所組成的無實體商品，Mars 將分享平常在工作中，會搜集哪些數據，以及如何進行推薦，讓用戶跳脫只能比價的框架，能在Tripresso團體旅遊搜尋引擎找到最適合他們的旅程～

Speaker Information

• Angie
企業策略部門的商業數據分析師，經濟及企管背景出身，在公司內部以資料分析挖掘問題，並推行如流程改善等解決方案。喜歡參與社群活動與各領域朋友們交流經驗，學習從不同的角度看世界。

• Yi-Chu Chen
現職是鹿羊科技的專案經理，算是一個什麼都需要做一點的工程師，在大學唸電子工程，研究所唸影像處理和機器學習，不過畢業當時，還沒有相關需求的職缺，就進入網路業，開始不斷學習的過程（不斷轉換語言跟框架），最喜歡網路將大家連在一起的特性，平常除了學習新技術外，也喜歡和來自不同背景的人溝通，希望能讓大家使用科技的門檻降低。

• Mia
現於Linker Networks擔任資料科學家，過去擔任過資料分析顧問，透過演算法以及機器學習去解決生活中/商業中會遇到的問題。曾於R-Ladies 柏林、里斯本跟台北做社群分享，現在也是R-Ladies Taipei以及Azure Taiwan Community的核心成員。

• Mars Weng
現任職於 Tripresso，擔任資料工程師，工作內容是旅行資料的爬蟲抓取與資料清理，以及規劃各種可能的資料整合應用。解決問題是 Mars 的核心精神，不只寫程式可以達到這個目的，培養夥伴學習程式也是一個很好的解答，目前擔任 PyLadies Hosts之一，負責帶領初探Python或是對網路爬蟲有興趣的人。

name: [Text mining] R與中文分詞
description:
1. Agenda

• 19:15-19:30 R Basic: 給初心者的統計概念與小故事

• 19:30-20:30 主議程: Word cloud in R @莊舒媛

• 20:30-20:50 閃電秀: 從外國語言到程式語言 @Pei Lee

• 20:50 - 自由交流時間

2. Talk Information

• Word cloud in R

在R軟體裡先做分詞處理，最後將結果儲存到資料庫中。在分詞處理上我們使用Rwordseg、jiebaR做分詞，依據分詞後的結果計算出頻率即可繪製文字雲。

• 從外國語言到程式語言

先分享一個免費的資料來源：全世界最大的社會事件開放資料庫 GDELT，以及實際應用。再來談談用外國語言工作一陣子後，改以程式語言安身立命的歷程：怎麼會從日文系跑去當數據分析師？

3. Speaker Information

• 莊舒媛

目前是國立臺北商業大學 研究生，在學生時期透過R軟體進行購物籃分析、關聯規則分析、網路爬蟲、LDA分析與類神經網路預測等研究。

• Pei Lee

大學主修日文跟廣告企劃，指考數學不及格，沒修過統計學，在傳產做過兩年日韓線採購，現在在當自己說出來都會心虛的數據分析師。剛過試用期不久，過著每天寫程式的生活，目前比較熟悉的語言是中文、日文、英文跟Python。

4. Host information

• Kristen Chan

name: [Crawler] 如何用數據打造最貼心的旅遊搜尋引擎
description:
1. Agenda


• 19:10 -19:30  R basic: [敘述統計] 相關性/相關係數、時間變數的資料型態、時間序列簡單看 @Ricci/旻均/舒瑜

• 19:30-20:30 主議程: 如何用數據打造最貼心的旅遊搜尋引擎 @Mars


• 20:30-20:50 閃電秀: Microsoft Azure Cognitive Services @姿君

• 20:50-21:10 閃電秀: 用 power BI 探索資料 @Claire

• 21:10 -   自由交流時間

2. Talk Information

• 如何用數據打造最貼心的旅遊搜尋引擎  
旅行是一個非常有趣的議題，背後是由極為複雜資訊所組成的無實體商品， Mars 將分享平常在工作中，會搜集哪些數據，以及如何進行推薦， 讓用戶跳脫只能比價的框架，能在Tripresso 團體旅遊搜尋引擎找到最適合他們的旅程～

• Microsoft Azure Cognitive Services
Microsoft Azure Cognitive Services 是一套集結合微軟研究成果的辨識 API，涵蓋內容十分廣泛，包含了表情與情緒偵測、視覺與語音辨識、語言理解、知識與搜尋等等，即使不懂 Machine Learning 也可以藉由輸入短短幾行程式碼，就建置出強大演算法的應用程式。 本次將介紹情緒偵測、視覺的部分，15 分鐘讓大家可以快速學會如何使用 Cognitive Service！

• 用 power BI 探索資料
懶得看密密麻麻的資料分布統計表格嗎？畫圖就對了！圖表可是速速看懂資料分布的超棒工具呢，要知道，畫圖治百病！（才怪）這次一起用 Power BI 來探索手上的資料吧！


3. Speaker Information

• Mars Weng 
現任職於 Tripresso，擔任資料工程師，工作內容是旅行資料的爬蟲抓取與資料清理，以及規劃各種可能的資料整合應用。解決問題是 Mars 的核心精神，不只寫程式可以達到這個目的，培養夥伴學習程式也是一個很好的解答，目前擔任 PyLadies Hosts 之一，負責帶領初探 Python 或是對網路爬蟲有興趣的人。

• 姿君
Beseye工程師，PyLadies 負責人之一，在公司負責影像處理與 Android 開發的部分，熱愛電腦科學，期待能夠跟大家一起追求神乎其技！

• Claire
知了新聞共同創辦人，〈互動地圖：雙北所得大解密〉作者。曾任 MIT Media Lab Changing Places Group 研究助理。沒有女朋友的少女心大叔魂死肥宅。意外的（？）pH值極低。最近喜歡乃木坂 46 的生田繪梨花跟 D3.js。夢想是減少這個世界上的資訊不對稱。

4. Host information

• Host

name: 如何打場黑客松
description:
1. Agenda

19:15~19:30 R basic: 遺漏值填補(Michelle)，資料型態轉換(Pepper)

19:30-20:15 如何打場黑客松@Luffy

20:30~20:45 閃電秀: 用人話寫程式的活文件@Joey

2. Talk Information

• 如何打場黑客松-跨國OpenData的取得及使用

分享參加黑客松比賽的經驗，如何從題目發想到做出prototype可以demo，以及分享自己跨領域學程式的經驗。

• 透明足跡介紹-環保相關OpenData

「透明足跡」是一個追蹤企業污染數據與環境表現的專案，這個網站是專案中的一個工具，透過視覺化系統，使艱澀的數據更好理解，讓全民都有機會掌握環境問題，並參與監督、檢舉，找出真正的環境兇手。

https://www.zeczec.com/projects/thaubing

• 用人話寫程式的活文件

現代軟體開發講究從需求、測試、開發、文件一氣呵成，其中包含：
該怎麼將需求實例化的過程，用人話的方式描述出來該怎麼從人話來設計驗收測試該怎麼從測試來驅動開發該怎麼將人話變成活文件

四件事就是同一件事
確保沒有浪費絲毫力氣在跟需求不相干的事物上確保開發前對驗收方式的理解有共識確保隨著軟體產品功能越來越多，花費在測試的時間與成本能趨於固定

3. Speaker Information

• Luffy
背景是台大經濟所，學習程式一年，主要使用Ｒ語言，參加過三次黑客松，今年七月參加的台大黑客松，團隊獲得第三名。

• Joey
Joey，大家都叫我 91，是 TDD 的狂熱者，將敏捷精神融入到自己的生活與人生。目前在 Odd-e 擔任敏捷教練，也是台灣團隊的負責人。參加過我 TDD 培訓課程的學員已超過 500 位，也有成功協助許多開發團隊引入敏捷開發的經驗，將自己定位在催化劑的角色，擅長讓團隊無痛有感的改善痛點，優化軟體設計及各角色之間協同合作的流程。

4.Code of Conduct
基本上這是一個女性學習社群，因此若你不是女性，但出現在我們的實體聚會的話，你很可能被要求以下行為：

• 發言的機會請優先留給女生

• 座位請優先保留給女生

• 必須對 R-Ladies Taipei 有貢獻，例如：提供高品質的 3分鐘技術閃電秀
